#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:15
msgid "The mirror tool mirrors a selection across a selected axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:17
msgid ""
"The mirror tool in *Edit Mode* is similar to :doc:`Mirroring in Object "
"Mode </modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/mirror>`. It is exactly "
"equivalent to scaling by -1 vertices, edges or faces around one chosen "
"pivot point and in the direction of one chosen axis, only it is "
"faster/handier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:23
msgid ""
"After this tool becomes active, select an axis to mirror the selection on"
" entering x,y, or z."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:25
msgid ""
"You can also interactively mirror the geometry by holding the :kbd:`MMB` "
"and dragging in the direction of the desired mirror direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:30
msgid "Axis of symmetry"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:32
msgid ""
"For each transformation orientation, you can choose one of its axes along"
" which the mirroring will occur."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:35
msgid ""
"As you can see, the possibilities are infinite and the freedom complete: "
"you can position the pivot point at any location around which we want the"
" mirroring to occur, choose one transformation orientation and then one "
"axis on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:41
msgid "Pivot point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:43
msgid ""
":doc:`Pivot points "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/index>` must be "
"set first. Pivot points will become the center of symmetry. If the widget"
" is turned on it will always show where the pivot point is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/mirror.rst:48
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-mesh-deform-mirror-center` the pivot point default to "
"median point of the selection of vertices in *Edit Mode*. This is a "
"special case of the *Edit Mode* as explained on the :doc:`pivot point "
"page </editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/index>`."
msgstr ""

